 United States Police say they found a 3-year-old girl wandering in a parking lot while her mother worked inside a South Florida strip club. Lauderhill police Lt. Michael Santiago says in a news release that someone called 911 early Tuesday after seeing a child roaming around. Santiago says the child-led officers to a vehicle that wasn’t running and had the back window cracked for ventilation. Police say about 30 minutes later 23-year-old Manouchika Daniels walked up and identified herself at the child’s mother. Continue reading Mother left child in car while working at strip club ―Police at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard